  - Q-Day-Prize
  - AI-agent
abstract: >
  An autonomous AI-agent–driven cryptanalysis pipeline for the Elliptic Curve
  Discrete Logarithm Problem (ECDLP), implemented end-to-end by Anthropic's
  Claude Sonnet 4.6 via the Claude Code interface, demonstrated on IBM
  Quantum Heron r2 hardware. The submission recovers a 22-bit (m=22) private
  key — six algorithmic steps beyond Lelli's 17-bit Q-Day Prize Round-1
  winner — using novel adaptive-counting and Stern-Brocot continued-fraction
  lift extraction techniques.
